D:\dev\guideXOSServer\kernel\arch\ia64\boot.s:7:* IA-64 boot differences from other architectures:
D:\dev\guideXOSServer\kernel\arch\ia64\boot.s:9:*   - Register Stack Engine (RSE) manages spill/fill automatically
D:\dev\guideXOSServer\kernel\arch\ia64\boot.s:10:*   - Instruction bundles are 128-bit (3 instructions + template)
D:\dev\guideXOSServer\kernel\arch\ia64\boot.s:13:*   - Predicate registers (p0-p63), p0 always true
D:\dev\guideXOSServer\kernel\arch\ia64\boot.s:34:* IA-64 IVT has 69 entry points, each 256 bytes (64 bundles).
D:\dev\guideXOSServer\kernel\arch\ia64\boot.s:41:.global ia64_ivt
